, indicating either suppressed [OI]\nemission in local galaxies or more extended, diffuse HI gas reservoirs traced\nby the HI 21-cm. Finally, we apply these empirical calibrations to the few\nhigh-redshift detections of [OI]-$63\\mu$m and [OI]-$145\\mu$m line transitions\nfrom the literature and further discuss the applicability of these conversion\nfactors to probe the HI gas content in the dense, star-forming ISM of galaxies\nat $z\\gtrsim 6$, well into the epoch of reionization.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 May 2023 07:23:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-10"}
